             <p class="comment">As someone who uses both Metro North and Amtrak to Hartford, the trains are sometimes standing room only and not full of illegal aliens. I am guessing many of the writers have never purchased a train ticket. Metro North stops in Fairfield County have overflow commuter parking lots that allow people to drive a short distance from home, park their car, and jump on a train to work. If similar services and parking was available in Wallingford, Meriden, Berlin, Windsor, Windsor Locks, and points north, many people could live north of New Haven and commute into Manhattan. This option would open up so many high paying jobs to additional Connecticut residents and be a positive move for the entire region.</p>
